Q1: WHY c3=55 IS CONSTANT
  n=11, k=5
  C(n,3) = 165
  Transitive triples = n*C(k,2) = 11*10 = 110
  Cyclic triples = 55
  Directed 3-cycles = 2 * 55 = 110
  This matches c3=55 vertex sets (c3_directed = 2*55 = 110)

  Formula: c3_cyclic = n(n-1)(n+1)/24 = 55
  Match: True
  p=3: c3 = 1
  p=5: c3 = 5
  p=7: c3 = 14
  p=11: c3 = 55
  p=13: c3 = 91
  p=17: c3 = 204
  p=19: c3 = 285
  p=23: c3 = 506

